---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending in -NESS: 7+ Letter Bingo Potential"
  description="Master -NESS ending words: DARKNESS (13), KINDNESS (13), WEAKNESS (17). High-scoring 7-8 letter bingo candidates with suffix strategy."
  keywords="scrabble words ending in ness, ness suffix scrabble, darkness scrabble score, weakness scrabble, ness bingo words, 8 letter scrabble words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Ending in -NESS: 7+ Letter Bingo Potential",
    "description": "Master -NESS ending words for high-scoring bingos in Scrabble.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ness" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring -NESS words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "WEAKNESS scores 17 points (W=4, K=5 contribute heavily), QUICKNESS scores 24, THICKNESS scores 22, and DARKNESS and KINDNESS each score 13. These 8-letter words all qualify for the 50-point bingo bonus." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Are -NESS words good for Scrabble bingos?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Excellent. -NESS words are typically 7-9 letters long, with many hitting the 7-8 letter bingo sweet spot. The suffix uses common tiles (N, E, S, S) making it easy to hold while building the root from incoming draws." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many tiles does the -NESS suffix use?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Four tiles: N, E, S, S. This means you only need 3 more tiles to form a valid 7-letter bingo, or 4 tiles for an 8-letter bingo. The double-S requirement is the main constraint — but with 4 S tiles in the bag, it is achievable." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -NESS: Bingo Potential</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The -NESS suffix transforms adjectives into nouns — and in Scrabble, it transforms your rack into bingo machines. At 7-8 letters, -NESS words are natural bingo candidates. The suffix uses common tiles (N, E, S, S), leaving you just 3-4 tiles away from a 50-point bonus.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles in suffix (NESS)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7-8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Typical word length</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingo bonus pts</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top -NESS Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Power Words</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WEAKNESS (17) · DARKNESS (13)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">KINDNESS (13) · BOLDNESS (11) · MADNESS (10)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">WEAKNESS scores highest among common -NESS words thanks to W(4) and K(5). All 8-letter -NESS words earn bingo bonus on top of tile score — WEAKNESS with bingo = 67 points minimum.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WEAKNESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DARKNESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KINDNESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOLDNESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SADNESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MADNESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Building Toward -NESS Bingos</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold N+E+S+S:</span> When you draw two S tiles plus N and E, you have the -NESS ending ready. Now look for 3-4 letter adjective roots in your remaining tiles or incoming draws.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Common valid roots:</span> DARK, KIND, WEAK, BOLD, MAD, SAD, GLAD, HARD, SOFT, WILD. If you hold -NESS tiles and draw any of these roots, play it immediately.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double-S challenge:</span> There are 4 S tiles in the bag. Holding 2 for -NESS means 2 fewer available for hooks. Weigh whether the bingo potential justifies holding both S tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">7-Letter vs 8-Letter -NESS Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7 Letters (3-letter root)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MADNESS · SADNESS · BADNESS · FITNESS · ILLNESS. Easier to complete — only 3 root letters needed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">8 Letters (4-letter root)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DARKNESS · KINDNESS · WEAKNESS · BOLDNESS · HARDNESS. Higher base scores — more premium letters in longer roots.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">-NESS words are <span class="text-white font-medium">almost never hookable</span>. Opponents cannot easily extend DARKNESS or KINDNESS. This makes them excellent defensive bingos — you score big without opening the board.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-ness/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending With -NESS: Complete List</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ful/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending in -FUL: Suffix Strategy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/eight-letter-bingos-guide/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Eight-Letter Bingos Guide</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check your -NESS word potential — free, instant, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
